      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="gpp_data"><a class="gpp_link" href="https://plus.google.com/112788519324230096635?rel=author">Edward Lathrop</a> <br /><span class="gpp_bio">Webmaster and Administrator of, as well as contributor to <a href="http://stopanxietystoppanic.com">Stop Anxiety Stop Panic</a>.</span></div><p>Natural <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/today" >Panic Attack</a> Remedy &#8211; Finding One That Really Works</p>
<div class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 310px"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Panic_attack.jpg" target="_blank"><img class="zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured" title="Panic attack" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/4/45/Panic_attack.jpg" alt="Panic attack" width="300" height="193" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Panic attack (Photo credit: Wikipedia)</p></div>
<p>by Melisa Gerrow</p>
<p>When anyone is afflicted by any kind of an illness, condition or malaise, he or she very often prefers to find a remedy that uses all natural ingredients. Normally, this is because no one wants a cure that may end up having more symptoms than the original ailment. For instance, you wouldn&#8217;t want to use a remedy for hang nail that would cause you to come down with hepatitis. It is certainly normal to be fearful of anything you put into your body or any method you may use as a potential remedy for anything. This is true whether you are trying to lose weight, cure a cold or prevent reoccurring <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/today" >panic attacks</a>.</p>
<p>Because of this, many people seek a vitamin an herb that would be helpful in alleviating panic and anxiety from their lives. Many people have tried, sometimes with a certain amount of success, using herbs such as, Kava Kava and St. John&#8217;s Wort. However, though many people are not aware of this, herbs can have just as many side effects as prescription drugs. Therefore, you shouldn&#8217;t go out on an herb buying spree without having been directed to do so by a medical professional.</p>
<p>It is widely accepted that a good B vitamin complex can be helpful when confronting a condition that is</p>
<div id="attachment_1001" class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 310px"><a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/B-VITIMINS.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1001" title="B VITIMINS" src="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/B-VITIMINS-300x224.jpg" alt="A Good B Vitamin" width="300" height="224" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Taking a B Complex Vitamin</p></div>
<p>brought on by nervous tension and anxiety. Many people have found help by including of good B complex vitamin in their daily routine. Of course, this is only helpful if the reason for your problem is that you are lacking a certain B vitamin. On the other hand, B vitamins are considered safe for anyone to take, while herbs are not always considered safe in all cases. The exception to this is niacin. Niacin is part of the complex and, when taken in excess it can cause a niacin flush. Therefore you should never exceed the recommended daily dosage for the B complex you are taking.</p>
<p>Recently, many people have found a, so-called, near vitamin named inositol to be very helpful when <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/today"  rel='nofollow' >dealing with panic</a> attacks. Inositol is found in many formulas which have been designed explicitly for the use of naturally calming nerves. Still, there are no guarantees inositol will cure your <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/today" >panic attack</a> syndrome. However, if you find a formula that includes it and there is nothing in the formula you have an aversion to, it might be worthwhile giving it a try. Most good formulas that can be helpful with panic attack include both inositol and taurine.</p>
