      <description>Edward Lathrop Webmaster and Administrator of, as well as contributor to Stop Anxiety Stop Panic. By Edward Lathrop One of the first problems a person suffering from panic attacks has to deal with is the fact he or she feels as &amp;#8230;&lt;p class="read-more"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/causes_of_anxiety/coping-panic-attacks/"&gt;Read more &amp;#187;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Here is a post from the blog &lt;a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com"&gt;Stop Anxiety Stop Panic&lt;/a&gt;.  Come visit and learn how to deal with and defeat anxiety and panic disorder.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/causes_of_anxiety/coping-panic-attacks/"&gt;Coping with Panic Attacks&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/stop-anxiety-stop-panic/Stop_Anxiety_Stop_Panic-Coping_with_Panic_Attacks.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="gpp_data"><a class="gpp_link" href="https://plus.google.com/112788519324230096635?rel=author">Edward Lathrop</a> <br /><span class="gpp_bio">Webmaster and Administrator of, as well as contributor to <a href="http://stopanxietystoppanic.com">Stop Anxiety Stop Panic</a>.</span></div><p><em> By Edward Lathrop</em></p>
<div id="attachment_941" class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 310px"><a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Panic-Alone.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-941" src="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Panic-Alone-300x199.jpg" alt="Alone with a Panic Attack" width="300" height="199" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Panic Sufferers do not have to be Alone</p></div>
<p>One of the first problems a person suffering from <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/today" >panic attacks</a> has to deal with is the fact he or she feels as if no one else understands what <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/today" >panic attacks</a> are all about. Because of this, people who have frequent or occasional panic attacks feel a sense of loneliness. They feel as if they are the only ones who have ever experienced the horrible sensations panic brings with it. They tend not to discuss this problem with anyone else because they feel they would be laughed at or at the very least, ignored.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/today" >Panic attack</a> syndrome makes a person feel misunderstood because they think those who have never experienced will be unsympathetic. They often feel as those who don&#8217;t experience panic will be arrogant towards those who do experience.</p>
<p>Fortunately, people who are unsympathetic to <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/today" >panic attack</a> sufferers are few and far between. First of all, even those who do not suffer anxiety know someone who does. Perhaps they have close friends or family members who suffer panic attack syndrome and therefore they have been exposed to it. These people have seen what it&#8217;s done to their friends and family members in therefore realize it is a very substantive issue. Besides this fact, hopefully the days are gone when people laugh at others who are suffering.</p>
<p>Beyond these facts is the fact many, many people suffer from panic attacks or have in the past. Obviously, these people totally understand what a panic attack sufferer is going through when he or she has these spells of panic. Also, people who have recovered from panic attack syndrome are usually very willing to help those who are now going through it. They realize it is not a weakness and certainly nothing to laugh at anybody for having.</p>
<p>Another way panic attack sufferers can be helped in their plight to cope with panic attacks is by realizing it is a condition that is widespread. There is a tendency to think whenever one is experiencing panic that no one else in the whole world is experiencing panic at that time. The truth of the matter is; if you&#8217;re in a crowded room and you are suffering panic, you will find there is probably someone else suffering panic at the same time.</p>
<p>Though it is certainly not a cure for panic, some comfort can be taken by knowing there are other people who understand totally and absolutely what you were going through when you are suffering a panic attack. In short, knowing there are others that are going through the same thing you are and realizing panic attack syndrome has been a widespread affliction for centuries can be a very helpful first step in coping with panic attacks.<!-- odiogo-notts-begin --></p>
