      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="gpp_data"><a class="gpp_link" href="https://plus.google.com/112788519324230096635?rel=author">Edward Lathrop</a> <br /><span class="gpp_bio">Webmaster and Administrator of, as well as contributor to <a href="http://stopanxietystoppanic.com">Stop Anxiety Stop Panic</a>.</span></div><p>By: Richard Tan</p>
<div id="attachment_931" class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 235px"><a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/Anxious.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-931" src="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/Anxious-225x300.jpg" alt="Anxiety Attack Coming On" width="225" height="300" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Anxiety Strikes</p></div>
<p>If you do your research, you will soon find out that the most common denominator of anxiety attacks is stress. It is a fact that stress is something that we cannot live without. At some level, stress is actually good, especially when it stays at a level that provides enough pressure on us to perform at our best. However, if it is going to go beyond that point, then it will cause something that is undesirable. At some point, stress can become a cause for a lot of diseases. With that, it is one of the many <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/stop_anxiety/panic-attacks/" >causes of panic attacks</a> and anxiety.</p>
<p>Therefore, if you want to prevent panic and anxiety attacks, you have to hatch a plan to control your level of stress by getting <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/stop_anxiety/anxiety-panic-attacks/" >anxiety and panic attacks</a> help. We all know that we may not be able to get rid of it totally; but, containing it at a certain level should prevent it from going overboard and cause the attacks.</p>
<p>To get rid of stress, one way of achieving it is to avoid the things that trigger it. For example, people get stressed out when they are getting too much pressure from their jobs. Juggling family and work obligations can also become too stressful for some. If your job gets you too stressed out, then the best way to keep the level of stress at bay is to give yourself a break by going on a vacation. For sure your employer would agree to it, since it is for your welfare.</p>
<p>To balance your family and work tasks, do not try to do everything by yourself. You can always ask your spouse to take some of the obligations as well. Try to set up a schedule in picking up or dropping off your kids at school. Take your turn in doing the laundry or the dishes. Share everything, so that you will be able to get some burden off your shoulders.</p>
<p>These are just simple tips you can follow as an <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/stop_anxiety/anxiety-panic-attacks/" >anxiety and panic attacks</a> help. However, when you follow these simple tips it would really take you a long way.</p>
