      <description>Edward Lathrop Webmaster and Administrator of, as well as contributor to Stop Anxiety Stop Panic.One of the most prevalent nervous symptoms is panic attacks. Panic attacks occur because nervousness has built to the point that the amount of adrenaline it &amp;#8230;&lt;p class="read-more"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/anxiety_disorder/nervous-symptoms/"&gt;Read more &amp;#187;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Here is a post from the blog &lt;a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com"&gt;Stop Anxiety Stop Panic&lt;/a&gt;.  Come visit and learn how to deal with and defeat anxiety and panic disorder.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/anxiety_disorder/nervous-symptoms/"&gt;Nervous Symptoms&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/stop-anxiety-stop-panic/Stop_Anxiety_Stop_Panic-Nervous_Symptoms.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="gpp_data"><a class="gpp_link" href="https://plus.google.com/112788519324230096635?rel=author">Edward Lathrop</a> <br /><span class="gpp_bio">Webmaster and Administrator of, as well as contributor to <a href="http://stopanxietystoppanic.com">Stop Anxiety Stop Panic</a>.</span></div><p>One of the most prevalent nervous symptoms is <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/today" >panic attacks</a>. <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/today" >Panic attacks</a> occur because nervousness has</p>
<div id="flickrImage_1" class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 171px"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/baileysjunk/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4047/4392781223_5fd6330623_m.jpg" alt="" width="161" height="240" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">I feel nervous</p></div>
<p>built to the point that the amount of adrenaline it has caused to run throughout the body has become maxed out. Is very common for a nervous person to suffer panic attacks and what is even more confounding is it is common for a person who is not seen as a nervous person to also suffer panic attacks.</p>
<p>Panic attacks stem from a condition known as anxiety disorder. Though this is a very daunting term it is important to understand that it is usually not a permanent condition. There are ways to <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/today"  rel='nofollow' >overcome anxiety</a> disorder and thus do away with the panic attacks that accompany this disorder. Anyone who suffers panic attacks is said to have an anxiety disorder however, not everyone who suffers an anxiety disorder will have panic attacks.</p>
<p>Either way, the road to recovery involves seeing a doctor about the symptoms the anxiety is causing. The reason this is important is a doctor can tell you whether any these symptoms lead to any physical ailments or they are all just a part of your anxiety disorder.</p>
<p>For instance, many people who suffer anxiety whether panic is accompanying the anxiety or not, will complain of tightness in the chest. Whenever anyone suffers tightness in the chest he or she should see a doctor very quickly so the doctor can tell him whether there is some problem with the heart or it the tightness is a symptom of some anxiety he or she has been suffering.</p>
<p>Once the anxiety sufferer has a clean bill of physical health, he or she can go about the business of overcoming the anxiety disorder or any of the other nervous symptoms that he or she may be experiencing.</p>
<p>There are many things that can help a person <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/today"  rel='nofollow' >overcome anxiety</a> disorder. Some of these are natural methods and most people prefer to try such methods first before they are put on a subscription that helps and anxiety sufferer live with anxiety disorder.</p>
<p>One such natural method that has helped many people <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/today"  rel='nofollow' >overcome panic</a> attacks and anxiety disorder in general is simply learning <a href="http://www.stopanxietystoppanic.com/stop_anxiety/anxiety-3/"  >what causes anxiety</a> and what is going on in the body when anxiety is occurring. It is also very helpful to many people when they understand just how common anxiety disorders are in that they are not alone when they are experiencing anxiety. Support groups are very helpful for this.</p>
<p>Still, the most important thing that leads to recovery of panic attacks and anxiety is knowing that physical disturbances that are felt during bouts of anxiety are just a manifestation of adrenaline and not true physical ailments, such as heart disease or hypertension. It is very important to note that only a doctor can tell you this for sure.</p>
